Bootstrap: docker
From: pytorch/pytorch:1.13.1-cuda11.6-cudnn8-runtime

%post
    apt-get update -y && apt-get install -y git && apt-get clean && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
    pip install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip
    pip install --no-cache-dir \
        "numpy<2" \
        opencv-python-headless==4.8.1.78 \
        scikit-image \
        pytorch-msssim \
        matplotlib \
        GPUtil \
        dominate \
        scipy \
        packaging

%labels
    Author vsc21212
    Model PSPStain
    BaseImage pytorch/pytorch:1.13.1-cuda11.6-cudnn8-runtime
    PyTorch 1.13.1+cu116
    Python 3.10
    Benchmark InViLabVirtualStainingBenchmark

%help
    PSPStain container for the InViLab virtual staining benchmark.
    Python 3.10, PyTorch 1.13.1 (cu116), CUDA 11.6 runtime.
    The cluster CUDA 12.x driver is backward compatible with this runtime.

    Training (BCI example):
      apptainer exec --nv \
        -B $VSC_DATA:$VSC_DATA \
        -B $VSC_SCRATCH/BCI.sqsh:/data/BCI:image-src=/ \
        $VSC_SCRATCH/containers/pspstain_nvidia.sif \
        python $VSC_DATA/projects/pspstain/code/pspstain/train.py \
          --dataroot /data/BCI ...

    Inference (BCI example):
      apptainer exec --nv \
        -B $VSC_DATA:$VSC_DATA \
        -B $VSC_SCRATCH/BCI.sqsh:/data/BCI:image-src=/ \
        $VSC_SCRATCH/containers/pspstain_nvidia.sif \
        python $VSC_DATA/projects/pspstain/code/pspstain/test.py \
          --dataroot /data/BCI ...
